
    <head>
        <title>Some Forms</title>
    </head>


        <form>
            <input type="text">
            <button>Submit!</button>
        </form>

* Need a way to access the element in the form: "id" is for css; "name" is to get value

<input type="text" name="fullname">

* Give it a label. Tag is for semantics, css. 

<label for="fullname">Full name:</label>

* Typical Properites:
placeholder="Your name"
minlength="3"
autofocus

* Other types of input:
<label for="fullname">Full name:</label>
<input name="fullname" type="text" autofocus placeholder="your name">
<label for="passwd">Password:</label>
<input name="passwd" type="password">

* Add a tad of style:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.simplecss.org/simple.css">

* More:
<div>
    <input type="date">
    <input type="color">
    <input type="email" name="myemail">
</div>

<div>
    Favorite color?
    <input name="color" type="radio" value="red"> Red
    <input name="color" type="radio" value="green"> Green
    <input name="color" type="radio" value="blue"> Blue
    <input name="color" type="radio" value="other"> Other
</div>

* Property of checked
